The paper proposes a neural architecture for recommendation systems, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multiple perspectives and attention mechanisms suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper may involve computer vision (cs.CV) if the recommendation system involves visual content.
